    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-03-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-03-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="342"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AA/3–1251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Indonesia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 12, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>977. Usgoc 495. Reur 954<note n="1" xml:id="d342fn1">In telegram 1226(<gloss
                            target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 954) from Djakarta, March 9, Ambassador
                        Cochran reported that Mr. Beam had again reiterated to his colleagues on the
                            <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> that the United States still
                        favored the complete dissolution of the <gloss target="#t_UNCI1"
                            >UNCI</gloss> at the earliest possible date because of Indonesia’s
                        opposition to its continuance (357.AA/3–951).</note> and 955 Dept concurs
                    your suggestion that <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> formally solicit
                    Netherlands and Indonesian views concerning Comm. Dept’s position still as you
                    stated that we advocate formal early dissolution. Believe that Comm’s action
                    shld at this time be aimed at eliciting formal expression views of parties on
                    this matter in view pending solution <gloss target="#t_KL1">KL</gloss> and
                        ex-<gloss target="#t_KNIL1">KNIL</gloss> problems.</p>
                <p>Sent to AmEmbassy Djakarta priority <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> 977;
                    repeated <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> New York 775, AmEmbassy The Hague
                    1033.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
